The time has come to tear down our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done, just a little decoration.
Remove the horrible electric fireplace and hearth. Encase the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand. Make a custom wardrobe.
We always start with a quick sketch in pencil...
The messy stage is completed.
I found several dead birds in the back of the chimney; all dried up :(
Ready for the plasterer next week
Pleased with the little alcove on the side
Insert the new wardrobe here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought of adding a charming little vent to prevent the chimney from getting damp
The chimney sweep took care of installing the hat and the windbreak. It should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. We're installing the floor tomorrow!
The cork underlayer is laid, I improvised a wood shavings extractor with a roll of toilet paper as an attachment for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Part of the boards are sorted and ready to be laid. We're just having a tea break
Well, progress was slow today because of super delicate cuts around the door posts to achieve a smooth transition into the hallway (which is also being laid). @user45@twitter.com cursed me
Done, but on our knees! Cherry on top: the unmanageable instructions for assembling the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
The hallway floor and all the skirtings remain to be done. The decorator is coming in a month, so in the meantime, at home, it's the chic of plaster without any primer.
Little DIY session in the evening to remove the lower sections of the door frames with a miter saw/with a chisel at the spot where we want the floor to be perfectly adjusted.
The cork underlayment for the hallway is also laid.
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then departure at 5 a.m. this morning to pick up Thing 1 from Heathrow, then a nap and the final stretch for the hallway; skirtings installed. We'll take care of the caulking when the adhesive has dried.
